def: Not usual; uncommon; rare; as, an unusual season; a person ofunusual grace or erudition.-- Un*u"su*al*ly, adv.-- Un*u"su*al*ness, n.
Expression of the passions; the science of the signs by whichhuman passions are indicated.
The flowing of different streams into one. [Obs.] Burton.
Overlapping each other; -- said of leaves whose bases arefolded so as to overlap and bestride the leaves within or above them,as in the iris.
The collection of postage stamps of various issues.
One who regards Father, Son, and Spirit as modes of being, andnot as persons, thus denying personal distinction in the Trinity.Eadie.
A level plain, usually with a steep front, bordering a river, alake, or sometimes the sea.
Finicky or pottering work; specif. (Fine Arts),
